description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for Band 5 Speech and Language Therapist to work within the Children’s Therapies Service in West Kent (Maidstone, Malling, Tonbridge, Tunbridge Wells and Sevenoaks). &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post involves working within the early years/clinic team - supporting children with speech, language and communication needs including stammering and voice and in the mainstream schools service. We offer assessment, direct and indirect interventions as well as providing training to education staff and parents.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We pride ourselves on the support and induction offered to new staff and this includes regular meetings with a line manager, access to supervision and access to in house training seminars - which cover a wide range of topics such as Early Years / Schools assessment and therapy / report writing / EHCP writing / School Years assessment / Fluency / Speech Disorders &amp; DVD / Hearing Impairment / Voice assessment and therapy. We also provide accredited training based on the caseload held. This will either be in- service by accredited trainers such as Derbyshire Language Scheme/Makaton/ VERVE PCI or by supporting external training e.g. Lidcombe /PCI. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will have opportunities to work alongside other SLTs, assistants, Physiotherapists, Occupational Therapists and Specialist Nurses as required. We are a large team with a wealth of experience and knowledge and we are committed to integrated working to ensure the best outcomes for our children and families.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a location, West Kent offers a combination of country side with a very easy access to London and railway/motorway networks.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We welcome visits to the department to meet the team. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applications for part-time arrangements will be also considered.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will be held on 27th November 2020.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
